## 5. API Routes Protection

All API routes must be protected with Clerk authentication.

```typescript
// app/api/decks/route.ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";

export async function GET() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  
  if (!userId) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: "Unauthorized" },
      { status: 401 }
    );
  }
  
  // Proceed with userId-filtered query
  const decks = await db
    .select()
    .from(decksTable)
    .where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));
  
  return NextResponse.json(decks);
}
```

---

## 6. Server Actions Protection

Next.js Server Actions must also verify authentication.

```typescript
"use server";

import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decksTable } from "@/db/schema";
import { revalidatePath } from "next/cache";

export async function createDeck(title: string, description: string) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  
  if (!userId) {
    throw new Error("Unauthorized");
  }
  
  const [newDeck] = await db
    .insert(decksTable)
    .values({
      userId, // ✅ Associate with authenticated user
      title,
      description,
    })
    .returning();
  
  revalidatePath("/decks");
  return newDeck;
}
```

---

## 7. Common Patterns Summary

### ✅ DO:
- Always call `await auth()` at the start of server actions and API routes
- Always check if `userId` exists before proceeding
- Always filter database queries by the authenticated `userId`
- Always verify ownership for nested resources (cards in decks, etc.)
- Use `and()` operator to combine ownership checks with other conditions
- Return appropriate error messages for unauthorized access

### ❌ DON'T:
- Never trust userId from client/props/parameters
- Never query data without filtering by authenticated userId
- Never skip authentication checks
- Never assume a resource belongs to a user without verification
- Never expose data from other users in responses

---

## 8. Integration with Drizzle Schema

All tables storing user data should have a `userId` field:

```typescript
// Reference: src/db/schema.ts
import { pgTable, serial, text, timestamp } from "drizzle-orm/pg-core";

export const decksTable = pgTable("decks", {
  id: serial("id").primaryKey(),
  userId: text("user_id").notNull(), // ✅ Links to Clerk user
  title: text("title").notNull(),
  description: text("description"),
  createdAt: timestamp("created_at").defaultNow().notNull(),
  updatedAt: timestamp("updated_at").defaultNow().notNull(),
});
```

Every table with user-specific data must include `userId` for proper filtering.

---

## 9. Error Handling

Use consistent error messages and HTTP status codes:

- **401 Unauthorized**: User is not authenticated
- **403 Forbidden**: User is authenticated but doesn't own the resource
- **404 Not Found**: Resource doesn't exist OR user doesn't own it (don't leak information)

```typescript
if (!userId) {
  return NextResponse.json(
    { error: "Unauthorized - please sign in" },
    { status: 401 }
  );
}

if (!deck) {
  return NextResponse.json(
    { error: "Deck not found" }, // Don't reveal if it exists but belongs to someone else
    { status: 404 }
  );
}
```

---

## 10. Verification Checklist

Before implementing any database operation, verify:

- [ ] `await auth()` is called to get userId
- [ ] userId existence is checked (user is signed in)
- [ ] Database query includes `.where(eq(tableName.userId, userId))`
- [ ] For nested resources, parent ownership is verified
- [ ] No client-provided userId is trusted
- [ ] Appropriate error handling is in place
- [ ] Delete operations verify ownership before executing

---

**Remember:** Security is not optional. Every data access point must enforce user isolation through Clerk authentication and proper query filtering.
